notesStmt.note: Only partially preserved, damaged and stained.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Four fragments of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Japhet ben Ali on Exodus.

msItem.title: Fragments of the commentary on Exodus 12

supportDesc.extent: Part I: Folios 1-34 Part II: Folios 35-83 Part III: Folios 84-87 Part IV: Folios 88 and 89.;

layoutDesc.layout: Part I: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 19; written lines: 19; The unpointed biblical text is embodied, followed by an Arabic translation. Part II: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 20-21; written lines: 20-21; Hebrew text is embodied. Part III: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 19; written lines: 19; Ruled with mastara. The pointed and accentuated Hebrew text is embodied, accompanied with an Arabic translation. Part IV: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 21; written lines: 21; Uniform layout.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, back flyleaf [i]v.
